# Web Input Handling â€“ Advent of Cyber 2025

## Overview
This challenge demonstrated how web applications process
user-controlled input and how improper handling can cause
security issues.

## Security Concept
Web vulnerabilities often occur when applications trust
user input without proper validation or sanitization.

## What Was Done
- Observed how the application handled user input
- Identified insecure input behavior
- Analyzed the impact of improper validation

## Tools Used
- Web browser
- Developer tools

## Outcome
The challenge showed how small logic issues can lead
to serious security problems.

## Key Takeaways
- User input should never be trusted
- Input validation is critical for security
- Web fundamentals are essential for pentesting
